  Description: As a strong playoff competitor year in and year out,  the Ohio Roar
    have a meticulous training regime they stick by. They perform detailed visualizations
    with thier players, playing situations out in the mind before they ever start
    practice. They believe this game is more mental than physical, and they keep
    their squad as focused as possible on winning. They have an unwavering belief
    that they will win the championship every year if they can maintain a clear picture
    of the path,  untainted by opponents trying to get in their head.
  CoachName: Jakobi Smithy
